The paper discusses the use of classical higher-order logic as a meta-logic for embedding other logics, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of this approach for realizing a universal logic reasoning approach, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of rational argumentation, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for using this approach as a communication layer between humans and machines, which is relevant to computer communication (cs.CC).
